The Blue Flame #10 is on sale today from @thevaultcomics 

Our final issue. The big finale. This series contains some of my most personal work, and drawing it took me to places interesting and unexpected both inward and out. It’s gratifying to reach our conclusion and I’m excited for readers to join us there, too. I’m thankful to @thevaultcomics for having me tell this rewarding story, and especially happy to have worked with such incredible people; @ifyoucantwell @kmichaelrussell @hassoe @aaronfisch @adrianwassel @timdanielcomics 

A special shout out to @yoshiyoshitani whose marvellous interconnected variant covers stunned me with every issue.

All my published credits for this year. At least all the ones I can think of. Certainly not everything I've drawn in 2022. 

This year I've drawn around 150 interior pages, a variety of covers and commissions, as well as gigs outside of comics. I also made my writing debut with two different projects. I'm very happy about that, and I hope to write some more.

I'm now working on a handful of big projects that won't be seen until mid-2023 and 2024. Although the coming year may appear to be quieter, it's already shaping up to be one of my busiest. The excitement never ends!

My sincere thanks to all my collaborators, editors, publishers, friends, and supporters for carrying me through another year.

Two weeks gone today and missing my dog, Harlowe. I don’t paint much these days but this was a nice way to remember her.

I’m happy to announce that I’m drawing issues 33 and 34 of Star Wars: Darth Vader for Marvel Comics.

It’s a super cool gig. Working with Greg Pak has been a nice experience and he’s written a pretty metal couple of issues for me to go ape on.

This marks the second time I’ve been lucky enough to have one all-time fav artists, Leinil Yu, illustrate the cover for the comic I’m working on.

Check it out!
